The paper deals with object recognition tasks and deep learning models, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on data efficiency and identifying redundancies also suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The observation of semantic correlations between required and redundant images may also relate to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
